      "role": "user",
      "content": "see but it's not just a \"calming effect.\" i've noticed it's always the same specific type of geometric repetition. it feels way more calculated than just \"marketing.\" like it's almost like a frequency or something that bypasses your brain and just hits your nervous system to make you passive. don't you think it's plausible that large corporations would use visual stimuli like that as a form of subtle social engineering? something to keep the masses from being too disruptive?",
