      "content": "exactly. \"nudge\" is a way polite people say \"manipulate.\" and if they're already using it for minor things like buying more stuff, what's stopping them from using it for actual social control? like, if you can use a pattern to make someone feel lethargic or submissive, you've basically found a way to pacify people without them ever knowing they're being messed with. can you look into the actual science of how specific repetitive visual frequencies affect cognitive resistance? i want to know if there's a way to identify these \"compliance\" patterns before i buy them.",
